<!-- The Essence -->
<section class="page-section section--bone">
  <div class="atelier-container atelier-prose">
    <h3 class="reveal">The Essence</h3>
    <p class="reveal" style="font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.625rem); color: var(--ink);">
      RALJE is a private atelier where a single moment — an engagement, a birth, an inheritance, a milestone, a devotion — is transformed into an heirloom, by the hands of four generations of goldsmiths rooted in Rajasthan, India.
    </p>
    <hr class="atelier-divider reveal">
  </div>
</section>

<!-- The Four Foundations -->
<section class="page-section section--parchment">
  <div class="atelier-container">
    <h3 class="reveal">The Four Foundations</h3>
    <h2 class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">WHAT WE STAND ON</h2>
    <hr class="atelier-divider reveal">

    <div class="foundation-grid">
      <div class="foundation-card reveal">
        <p class="foundation-card__name" style="color: var(--ink);">Heritage</p>
        <p class="foundation-card__desc" style="color: var(--ink);">
          Four generations of goldsmithing experience from Rajasthan, India — the historical centre of jewelled arts. This is not a marketing story; it is the reason we can work across Polki, Kundan, Meenakari, Thewa, and modern techniques with equal fluency.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="foundation-card reveal">
        <p class="foundation-card__name" style="color: var(--ink);">Innovation</p>
        <p class="foundation-card__desc" style="color: var(--ink);">
          Heritage without innovation is a museum. RALJE bridges traditional Rajasthani craft with modern technology — 3D jewellery design, photorealistic rendering, precision casting. The client sees the piece before it exists.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="foundation-card reveal">
        <p class="foundation-card__name" style="color: var(--ink);">Personalisation</p>
        <p class="foundation-card__desc" style="color: var(--ink);">
          There is no catalogue. There is no showroom floor. Every RALJE piece is designed around a specific person and a specific moment. The consultation ensures we understand both deeply.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="foundation-card reveal">
        <p class="foundation-card__name" style="color: var(--ink);">Legacy</p>
        <p class="foundation-card__desc" style="color: var(--ink);">
          The finished piece is not a product. It is a legacy object — something the client will wear, pass down, and attach meaning to for generations.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Four Generations -->
<section class="page-section section--bone">
  <div class="atelier-container">
    <div class="maker-profile">
      <div class="maker-profile__image reveal">
        {{ 'ralje-bench-heritage.jpg' | asset_url | image_tag: loading: 'lazy', alt: 'The goldsmith bench — four generations of craft' }}
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="atelier-label reveal">The Lineage</span>
        <h2 class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">FOUR GENERATIONS</h2>
        <hr class="atelier-divider reveal">
        <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
          The Soni family's goldsmithing lineage is rooted in Rajasthan, India — the historical centre of jewelled arts on the subcontinent. Rajasthan is where Polki, Kundan, Meenakari, Thewa, Jadau, and Navratna were invented, refined, and handed down through generations of master goldsmiths.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">
          Rahul Soni is the fourth generation of his family in this craft. From age ten, he worked beside his father on a Rajasthani bench — first repairing silver, then moving into the full range of traditional work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- From Rajasthan to Santa Ana -->
<section class="page-section section--ink">
  <div class="atelier-container atelier-prose">
    <h3 class="reveal">From Rajasthan to Santa Ana</h3>
    <p class="reveal">
      In 2017, Rahul came to the United States. He visited the jewellery halls of American malls. What he found was dry ground — generic forms made at scale, creativity absent, none of the inherited arts that make a piece into a one-of-a-kind.
    </p>
    <p class="reveal">
      He returned to the work — but slowly, and completely. Over three years, he added the disciplines the workshop in Rajasthan could not teach: three-dimensional modelling, rendering, the ability to show a client a piece that does not yet exist, in the light it will wear.
    </p>
    <p class="reveal">
      The first piece of the new era was a ring — for Francisca, his wife. Not bought. Designed, iterated, cast, set, delivered. A private commission that became the template for everything that followed.
    </p>
    <blockquote class="reveal"><p>Heritage craft, modern vision.</p></blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- The Evolving Craft Library -->
<section class="page-section section--bone">
  <div class="atelier-container">
    <h3 class="reveal">The Evolving Craft Library</h3>
    <h2 class="reveal" style="color: var(--ink);">DISCIPLINES</h2>
    <hr class="atelier-divider reveal">

    <table class="craft-table reveal">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Discipline</th><th>Application at RALJE</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Polki</td><td>Uncut natural diamonds set in gold foil — the traditional bridal art of Rajasthan.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Kundan</td><td>Fine gold foil setting, 24-karat, built layer by layer around the stone.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Meenakari</td><td>Vitreous enamel fired into the metal. The deep blues, greens, and reds of Rajasthani manuscript art.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thewa</td><td>Fused gold on coloured glass, an art indigenous to Pratapgarh.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Jadau</td><td>The embedded setting tradition — stones pressed directly into soft gold.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Navratna</td><td>Nine-gem sacred compositions — the astral gems of Indian tradition.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>3D Modelling</td><td>CAD design in Rhino/Matrix — the client sees the piece before it exists.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Rendering</td><td>Lifelike visualisation for client approval, lit as the piece will wear.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Precision Casting</td><td>3D-printed wax model, investment cast in gold or platinum.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Who We Are For -->
<section class="page-section section--ink">
  <div class="atelier-container atelier-prose">
    <h3 class="reveal">A Word on Whom We Serve</h3>
    <p class="reveal">
      RALJE is for the person marking a moment of irreversible significance and who believes that the object carrying that meaning must be worthy of it. This person does not browse. They inquire.
    </p>
    <p class="reveal" style="opacity: 0.6;">
      RALJE is not for the person seeking a gift under deadline, a fashion ornament, or a trend. We will decline those requests, kindly.
    </p>
